verses.roman:
ei-mata nānā raṅge dina kata gela
jagannāthera ratha-yātrā nikaṭa ha-ila

synonyms: ei-mata—in this way; nānā raṅge—in great jubilation; dina kata—some days; gela—passed; jagannāthera—of Lord Śrī Jagannātha; ratha-yātrā—the car festival; nikaṭa ha-ila—became nearer.
translation: In this way, the Lord passed some days in great jubilation. Then the car festival of Lord Jagannātha approached.
